<title type="html"><![CDATA[Famicombox (Black Carts)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6118&amp;p=57827#p57827"><![CDATA[
AFAIK from random sources about the hotel Nintendo operations, the famicombox cartridges use a different lockout chip from all other regions, and suposedly like select PAL B cartridges, the PRG and CHR chips are wired to the lockout chip to disable when not authorized by the 'lock' chip.<br /><br />I'd love to see the front/back scans of the PCB of one of these games, since a quick look at the wiring could possibly prove this theory.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=26">AWal</a> — Tue Mar 09, 2010 7:06 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
